body:
You are filing a lot of issues with C# tag in it. It is important to realize that we do not ship implementation in C#. Everything is implemented in C++. C# is just an API.
Custom operators to be implemented in C++, that library in turn is loaded by onnxruntime library. You use C# to run inference using public C API as usual.

@tianleiwu
Based on the question and tentative answer here:[ Is there a difference between how python and c api and c++ wrapper accessing the contributed operators?](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/discussions/11726)

Currently c api provide custom operator registration. 

There is no way to invoke contributed operator through the c api, therefore not possible through c++ wrapper AND c#

issue.title: [Feature Request] Classify Contributed Ops

labels.name: feature request
labels.description: request for unsupported feature or enhancement

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
### Describe the feature request

Currently there is no categorization of [contributed Ops](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/main/docs/ContribOperators.md) into e.g. NLP, Vision, and Audio 

All are under ONE same namespace: **com.microsoft**

The suggestion is to split these Ops into the following categories

e.g.

- [ ] com.microsoft.nlp
- [ ] com.microsoft.vision
- [ ] com.microsoft.audio

For those Ops that are non-specific to any one of the above categories, they stay with 

- [ ] com.microsoft

### Describe scenario use case

To democratize the use of these ops, especially for new users, for users interested on e.g. NLP, they could look into the following namespeace

##### nlp
com.microsoft.nlp
- [com.microsoft.nlp.BeamSearch](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/main/docs/ContribOperators.md#com.microsoft.BeamSearch)
- [com.microsoft.nlp.GreedySearch](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/main/docs/ContribOperators.md#com.microsoft.GreedySearch)

##### vision
com.microsoft.vision

- [com.microsoft.vision.CropAndResize](https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/main/docs/ContribOperators.md#com.microsoft.CropAndResize)
